  "__fixture__": {
    "name": "shared_debug_control_alpha_baseline",
    "scenario": "One alpha page covers a shared debug session with all five typed control states present: a session observer in view_only_observer; a follower in follow_presenter_observer bound to the driver as follow target; a requesting participant in request_control_pending; an active driver in active_control_grantee bound to an admitted one-shot grant; and a revoked grantee in control_revoked citing the upstream revocation. Two presenter handoffs exercise presenter_role_accepted (handoff completed) and presenter_role_auto_observer (presenter stepped away and the role auto-downgraded to view-only). Audit events name control_active_started, control_revoked, follow_engaged, follow_released, and presenter_handoff_resolved on the local audit stream, plus an audit_denial_emitted that names a replay denial. Two continuity observations record owner_debug_authority_preserved_after_grantee_revoked and grantee_demoted_observer_no_step_injection so local debug authority is preserved without silent stepping or breakpoint injection."
  },
